major events since fw de 
klerk was inaugurated as president on sept 20 
sept 20 de klerk takes the oath of office at the union 
buildings in pretoria pledges to seek a south africa free of 
domination and oppression 
oct 2 officials of the national government negotiate for the 
first time with activists on possible solutions to a threeyear 
rent boycott in soweto the countrys largest black township 
oct 11 de klerk confers for three hours with anglican 
archbishop desmond tutu and two other antiapartheid church leaders 
oct 15 on de klerks orders the government unconditionally 
frees eight prominent longterm political prisoners including 
walter sisulu a senior leader of the outlawed african national 
